Tony Blair said he would use the opportunity to return as Prime Minister - but admits that a comeback is unlikely.
In an interview on the occasion of the fifth anniversary of his departure from Office this evening the 59-year-old announced his views on various political topics.
Since his resignation in June 2007 after a decade as head of State has Blair largely avoided to comment on British politics and limited his comments on foreign policy and his role as Envoy of the Quartet of peacemakers in the Middle East.
On the question of whether he gladly would return to the post of Prime Minister, Blair was quoted as London by the evening standard from the words: "Yes, sure, but it is unlikely this would happen, so..."
